  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nI installed a new three node quorum raft network using [Quorum Maker](https://github.com/settlemint/quorum-maker) and can deploy my contracts (they and truffle works like expected on a Parity PoA network). \r\n\r\nApart from the less pretty output, it all appears well. Contacts and transactions show up in the explorer as well.\r\n\r\n```./deploy.sh mintquorumnet --reset\r\n\r\n> @settlemint/mint-demo@0.0.0-development truffle /Users/roderik/Development/mint-demo\r\n> truffle \"migrate\" \"--network\" \"mintquorumnet\" \"--reset\"\r\n\r\n\r\nCompiling your contracts...\r\n===========================\r\n> Everything is up to date, there is nothing to compile.\r\n\r\nRunning migration: 1_initial_migration.js\r\nReplacing Migrations...\r\nMigrations: 0x1e7BeF833D0843aaf72997DE7F56d9E6fA59A66E\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 2_deploy_gatekeeper.js\r\nReplacing GateKeeper...\r\nGateKeeper: 0x9Bb76a9662C7b4707630b0Bff5f3b58b2D0dEe6a\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 3_deploy_roles.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nDeploying AdminRoleRegistry...\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 4_deploy_expenses.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nDeploying ExpenseRegistry...\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 5_deploy_medicine.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nAdminRoleRegistry: 0x79fB999364c5b66999544eA447E5d6678209826B\r\nDeploying MedicineRegistry...\r\nExpenseRegistry: 0xdA48BAe178B7C81B5968813251C404392b19E171\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 6_deploy_shares.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nDeploying ShareRegistry...\r\nMedicineRegistry: 0x63aD86f7ae6Fa3e3ed1E4F1beD942a3F8BAa949f\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 7_deploy_loan.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nDeploying ExpenseFactory...\r\nShareRegistry: 0x0Db54766e9a25F0f4B86fbBB828f35b7c5b4B760\r\nROLE: ROLE_CUSTOMER\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 7_deploy_loans.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nDeploying MedicineFactory...\r\nDeploying LoanRegistry...\r\nDeploying CustomerRoleRegistry...\r\nExpenseFactory: 0x4384B999dcA2212583f897D85b6B8175686e5137\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\n```\r\n\r\nExcept in the son files of e.g. ExpenseFactory the networks section looks like \r\n\r\n```\r\n  \"networks\": {},\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhile I expected 0x4384B999dcA2212583f897D85b6B8175686e5137 mentioned in there.\r\n\r\nMy config is:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    mintquorumnet: {\r\n      provider: () => {\r\n        return new HDWalletProvider(\r\n          process.env.ETHEREUM_DEPLOYER_SEED ||\r\n            'robot robot robot robot robot robot robot robot robot robot robot robot',\r\n          'http://xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx:22000'\r\n        );\r\n      },\r\n      gasPrice: '0',\r\n      network_id: '*',\r\n      websockets: true,\r\n      production: false,\r\n      type: 'quorum',\r\n    },\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: OSX\r\n* Ethereum client: Quorum 2.2.1\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.0.12\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v11.14.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.9.0",
