    "body": "I think it is because of a wrong handling of async migrations. A typical v4 issue that has not happened since v5.\r\n\r\n```\r\nRunning migration: 1_initial_migration.js\r\nDeploying Migrations...\r\nMigrations: 0x2Cf26c56291ccB3F33caAD5b78fA1D5646d4aD39\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 2_deploy_gatekeeper.js\r\nDeploying GateKeeper...\r\nGateKeeper: 0x89314CBEf86Ed46c3E73760efd7ABe3f12913Bd4\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 3_deploy_roles.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nDeploying AdminRoleRegistry...\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 4_deploy_expenses.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nAdminRoleRegistry: 0xfC078a12A3938C1618debC3BF88296a2C9cAF5D0\r\nDeploying ExpenseRegistry...\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 5_deploy_medicine.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nDeploying MedicineRegistry...\r\nExpenseRegistry: 0xCe09F4Bba69ed40f8C561f335aA1E21DdEFFb561\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 6_deploy_shares.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nDeploying ShareRegistry...\r\nMedicineRegistry: 0x2DEC2B8BcC8905f9FB53Ba1beCa331cE766848b8\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 7_deploy_loan.js\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nROLE: ROLE_CUSTOMER\r\nDeploying CustomerRoleRegistry...\r\nDeploying ExpenseFactory...\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\nRunning migration: 7_deploy_loans.js\r\nShareRegistry: 0x926C59162015ac83761147b4834944ccCcaCDE81\r\nSaving successful migration to network...\r\nDeploying LoanRegistry...\r\nDeploying MedicineFactory...\r\nCustomerRoleRegistry: 0xaF098F5E65C3C7D33fD6fB893E75d4e083bCD93f\r\nSaving artifacts...\r\n```\r\n\r\nAcross the list you see \"RoleRegistries\" being deployed., but this is all in migration nr 3 and there are more. I checked all the migrations and they all properly await deployments (and works on Parity) so I think there is a promise checking that is wrong for quorum deployments.",
